This is OEChem data manipulation scripts

First you need to build index DB with position, size and filename of each molecule.
Needs about 2 hours to finish (no need to run, already builded)

~/scripts25/indexer.py --readfromdir ~/ --db ~/scripts25/new.sqlite


To extract molecules to tar.gz file after building index:

~/scripts25/extractor25.py  --readfromdir ~/ --db ~/scripts25/index.sqlite --input-file in.txt --output-file results.tgz

Index data can be extracted to csv file for instance:
sqlite3 -header -csv {} 'select sid,cid from oechem_data' > output.csv

This csv can be imported to mysql  (use substance1.sql as example. `mysql yourdbname < substance1.sql`)

